## **Executive Summary**
Dover Corporation (DOV) demonstrates robust operational resilience and financial discipline amid a challenging macroeconomic environment. Despite a **16% organic revenue decline in Q2**, the company delivered **strong decremental margins (27%)**, **exceeded free cash flow (FCF) guidance by $78M YoY**, and reinstated EPS guidance—signaling a potential inflection point in its recovery trajectory. With proactive cost controls, disciplined working capital management, and a resilient backlog, DOV is well-positioned to capitalize on industrial end-market stabilization in H2 2024.

